---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About">
	<div class="p-10">
        <div>
            <p>cd ./about/</p>
        </div>
    	<div class="grid bg-black bg-opacity-70">
			<!-- Objective -->
			<h1 class="p-4 text-center">
				Driven computer science student with a curiosity and passion for learning, </br>
				looking for opportunities to gain more technical skills and expand knowledge.
			</h1>
	
		<div>
			<h1 class="section-title">Education</h1>
			<div class="p-4 ml-4 flex gap-4">
				<p class="info">Sept 2024 to June 2028</br></br>Sept 2020 to June 2024</p>
				<p class="info">
					Pursuing a Bachelor of Science in Computer Science Systems</br>
					4.0 GPA, Oregon State University</br>
					High School Diploma, Cedarcrest Highschool</br>
					4.0 GPA, Valedictorian
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<!-- Skills -->
		<div>
			<h1 class="section-title">Technical Skills</h2>
			<ul class="list-disc p-4 ml-8">
				<li>Proficient in C#, Java, Python, and C++</li>
				<li>Familiar with Git and its functions</li>
				<li>Experienced in Unity 2D and 3D, including online multiplayer</li>
				<li>Experience in publishing apps on the iOS App Store </li>
				<li>Machine Learning, Deep Learning</li>
				<li>Flutter/Andriod Studio</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		
		<div>
			<h1 class="section-title">Experience</h2>
			<div class="p-4 ml-4 flex gap-4">
				<p class="info">October 2024 to Present</br></br></br></br></br></br></br></br>April 2021 to Present</p>
				<p class="info">
					Star Labs (URSA Engage)</br>
					Research Assistant in Maching Learning</br>
					Currently working on a project with two other students that implements a large language model into an app, using it to</br>
					provide nutrition advice to users. Implemented RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation) using Python to improve the</br>
					accuracy of the LLM when generating recipes, and to produce results based on the documents embedded into the</br>
					database.</br></br>
	
					Nutron Labs</br>
					Co-Founder</br>
					In my time at Nutron Labs, I was the sole developer in the publishing and development 5 apps </br>
					on the iOS App Store. These products, all developed in Unity, required a different set of skills to </br> 
					develop each and amassed over 400 downloads among all of them. </br>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		
		<div>
			<h1 class="section-title">Clubs and Leadership</h2>
			<div class="p-4 ml-4 flex gap-4">
				<ul class="list-disc p-4">
					<li>Current Webmaster OSU App Development Club</li>
					<li>Active member in the Google Developer Club and ACM</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
    	</div>
    </div>
</div>
</Layout>

<style>

	.section-title {
		font-weight: 500;
		display: inline-block;
		border: bottom;
		border-bottom: 2px solid var(--matrix-green);	
		padding: 0 16px 8px 16px;
	}

	.info {
		color: var(--matrix-green);
	}
	.grid {
        border-color: var(--matrix-green);
        border-width: 2px;
        border-radius: 20px;
        padding: 20px;
        display: grid;
        justify-items: start;
        row-gap: 50px;
        column-gap: 100px;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(1, 1fr);
        box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.5);
    }

	.hover\:shadow-glow:hover {
        box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.5);
    }

	h1 {
		font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
		font-size: 30px;
		margin-top: 0.25em;
	}

	p {
		font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
		padding: 10px 10px;
		color: var(--matrix-green);
		font-weight: normal;
	}
</style>
